title: Messaging startup Symphony lands $100 million from Google, others
text:
Photo: Nathaniel Y. Downes, The Chronicle From left, Aaron Scales, Platform Engineer and Rob Wisniewski, VP of Engineering take a break from work to play a round of table tennis in the offices of Symphony on Friday, Oct. 9, 2015 in Palo Alto, Calif. From left, Aaron Scales, Platform Engineer and Rob Wisniewski, VP...
Symphony Communication Services , a Palo Alto startup that offers messaging tools for businesses, said Monday it raised more than $100 million in new capital, from investors including Google Inc.
